import math
import numpy as np
from matplotlib import pyplot as plt
from matplotlib import animation, rc
from IPython.display import HTML

def update(t):
    plt.cla() #
    v = 0.34
    om1 = 0.25
    om2 = 0.2
    T1 = 2*math.pi/om1
    T2 = 2*math.pi/om2
    lam1 = v*T1
    lam2 = v*T2
    th1 = -math.pi/2
    th2 = math.pi/2


    x = np.linspace(0,14*math.pi,200) #(start,stop,num=50,endpoint=true,...)
    y1 = np.sin(2*math.pi*(t/T1-x/lam1)+th1)
    y2 = np.sin(2*math.pi*(t/T2-x/lam2)+th2)
    plt.ylim(-2.1,2.1)
    plt.plot(x,y1+y2)
    plt.title('Time'+str(t))

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8.0,4.0))
movie =  animation.FuncAnimation(fig,update,frames=100,interval=50)
rc('animation',html='jshtml')
movie
